This file explain how to install TurtleBots using Makefile

Short way:
    make
    sudo make install

You can change the "prefix" (by default "/usr/local")
or any other vartiables of instalation
For example to intall in /home/myhome type this
    make
    make prefix=/home/myhome install

The Makefile meets the GNU standards (or at least most of them)
sow you can change the default installation variables...
    prefix = /usr/local
    bindir = $(prefix)/bin
    datarootdir = $(prefix)/share
    datadir = $(datarootdir)
    sysconfdir = $(prefix)/etc
    glbconfdir = /etc
    docdir = $(datarootdir)/doc/turtlebots
    infodir = $(datarootdir)/info
    localedir = $(datarootdir)/locale


The follow objetives are defined:
    help: Show this. "Yes! you're watching this right now"
    all : compile all requerid.
    xo : Generate the XO distribuible package
    dev: compile all necessary for TurtleArtButia
                 and make a developed sugar install
                 this allow to work and easy change the code
    install: install the activity (use $prefix)
    uninstall: unistall the activity (use $prefix)
    clean: clean all compiled/generated files


Makefile suport the follow parameters:

    TURTLEBLOCKS_VERSION=[version or commit]
        This change the default version of turtleblocks to use
        in the creation of TurtleBots (internaly a git checkout is done)
    EXTRAS_VERSION=[version or commit]
        This change the default version of traductions to use
        in the creation of TurtleBots (internaly a git checkout is done)
    NXT_VERSION=[version or commit]
        This change the default version of nxt plugin to use
        in the creation of TurtleBots (internaly a git checkout is done)
    WEDO_VERSION=[version or commit]
        This change the default version of wedo plugin to use
        in the creation of TurtleBots (internaly a git checkout is done)
    NOGIT=true
        if setting "true" then no git checkout is used, turtlebots will
        be created using the current state of plugins/mainline directorys

    SHELL=/bin/sh  (by default)
    LESS=less      (by default)
        usefull program internaly used in Makefile

    BUILDDIR = tmp  (by default)
        This change the directory were turtlebots is compiled

    INSTALL = install  (by default)
    INSTALL_PROGRAM = $(INSTALL)
    INSTALL_DATA = ${INSTALL} -m 644
        This change the program used to intall the TurtleBots


